    "File-level granularity is the most prevalent (nearly 80%), whereas statement-/line-level granularity receives less emphasis [333,345].• Training dataset size.",
    "In the majority of studies, within-version defect prediction is the norm, leading to training sets typically comprising fewer than 1000 instances.",
    "Notably, only a handful of change-level defect prediction studies leverage notably larger datasets, with instance counts reaching tens of thousands [329].In summary, existing studies primarily concentrate on projects involving a small number of programming languages, mainly focusing on coarse-grained defect prediction.",
    "In particular, the training set sizes for deep learning are often limited.",
    "Challenges and opportunitiesWhile numerous studies have put forward different defect prediction methodologies, several significant challenges hinder the development of accurate and cost-effective approaches for defect prediction."
